1. Java Code (Login.java)
(5 lines. Use nano Login.java to create it.)

Java
import java.util.Scanner;
class Login {
    public static void main(String[] a) {
        var s = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("User: ");
        String u = s.next();
        System.out.print("Pass: ");
        // Check if user is "admin" and password is "123"
        System.out.println((u.equals("admin") && s.next().equals("123")) ? "Success" : "Denied");
    }
}
2. Dockerfile
(3 lines. Use nano Dockerfile to create it.)

Dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk
COPY Login.java .
CMD ["java", "Login.java"]
3. Execution in Terminal
You MUST use the -it flag. This stands for "Interactive Terminal" and allows you to type inside the container.

Build:

Bash
sudo docker build -t login-term .
Run (The Important Part):

Bash
sudo docker run -it login-term
